  <title>Remove apps and folders from the desktop</title>

  <steps>
    <title>To remove an app from your desktop:</title>
    <item>
      <p>Click and hold the app icon you want to remove.</p>
    </item>
    <item>
      <p>Keeping the mouse button pressed, drag the app icon on top of <media
      its:translate="no" type="image" mime="image/png"
      src="figures/eos-icon-more-apps.png">the plus button</media>.</p>
      <media its:translate="no" type="image" mime="image/gif" src="figures/eos-desktop-delete-app.gif"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <p>You will notice that the <gui>More Apps</gui> icon will become a trash
      can icon.</p>
    </item>
    <item>
      <p>Just drop the icon there to remove the app from your desktop.</p>
      <media its:translate="no" type="image" mime="image/png" src="figures/eos-desktop-delete-notification.png"/>
    </item>
  </steps>

  <p>The <gui>More Apps</gui> icon will always be the last icon on your desktop.
  </p>

  <note>
    <p>Removing the app from your desktop doesn't remove it from the system. If
    you want to delete the app entirely from the system to make storage space
    available, you can do it from the <app>App Center</app>.</p>
  </note>


 <steps>
    <title>To remove a folder from your desktop:</title>
    <item>
      <p>First, you'll need to remove all of the apps within the folder you'd like
      to delete. Follow the steps above and drag each app outside of the folder. 
      You can then leave each app on your desktop, or you can move the apps to another
      folder or the trash.</p>
    </item>
    <item>
      <p>Once the folder you want to remove is empty, click and hold the folder.</p>
    </item>
    <item>
      <p>Keeping the mouse button pressed, drag the folder on top of <media
      its:translate="no" type="image" mime="image/png"
      src="figures/eos-icon-more-apps.png">the plus button</media>.</p>
      <media its:translate="no" type="image" mime="image/gif" src="figures/eos-desktop-delete-app.gif"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <p>You will notice that the <gui>More Apps</gui> icon will become a trash
      can icon.</p>
    </item>
    <item>
      <p>Just drop the folder there to remove it from the desktop.</p>
      <media its:translate="no" type="image" mime="image/png" src="figures/eos-desktop-delete-notification.png"/>
    </item>
  </steps>


